events.description: Report showing US companies announced 108.4K job cuts last month, the highest January total since 2009.
Weekly report showing claims rose to 231K, exceeding forecasts.
Private-sector job growth data that fell short of expectations.
The US Treasury maintained its issuance guidance, favoring short-term bills.

facts.fact_text: The yield on the US 10-year Treasury note fell 4 bps to 4.24% on Thursday.

evidences.evidence_text: The yield on the US 10-year Treasury note fell 4 bps to 4.24% on Thursday, hitting its lowest level in about a week
